[2] China/Myanmar
Date: 11 Mar 2004
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Newsday [edited]
<http://www.newsday.com/sports/soccer/wire/sns-ap-soc-china-match-canceled,0,467247.story?coll=sns-ap-soccer-headlines>

China Cancels Soccer Game Against Myanmar
--------------------------
China has called off an exhibition soccer match with Myanmar because of the
bird flu outbreak.
The match was a warmup for China's national squad before its World Cup
qualifier against Hong Kong in 3 weeks, the official Xinhua News Agency
reported Wednesday.
"There are restrictions for Myanmar players to enter China since they are
from a bird flu-hit area," Xinhua said, citing state-run media.
The organization has already canceled friendlies against Syria and Viet
Nam, Xinhua said.
